'''Michel Vorm''' ({{IPA-nl|<U+02C8>mi<U+0283><U+025B>l <U+02C8>v<U+0254>rm}}; born October 20, 1983 in [[Nieuwegein]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[association football|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]], currently playing for [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]]. He is also renowned for his remarkable penalty saving abilities, earning him the nickname 'The Penalty Killer'.

==Club career==
===FC Den Bosch===
To get more experience, Vorm went for one season to [[FC Den Bosch]] on a loan.  He made his debut on 12 August 2005 against [[FC Emmen]].  That season he played 35 matches for FC Den Bosch.

===FC Utrecht===
On 19 August 2006, Vorm made his debut for FC Utrecht in against [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]]. Although he joined FC Utrecht as the third goalkeeper, behind [[Franck Grandel]] and [[Joost Terol]], his pre-season performance impressed manager [[Foeke Booy]], and saw him being promoted to the first choice at the start of the league. During his first season Vorm played 33 out of 34 games, and his position as first goalkeeper remained unchallenged throughout his time at Utrecht. Vorm only missed some matches during the 2007-08 season due to knee and shoulder injuries. He left Utrecht at the start of the 2011-12 season, having played 136 games in the [[Eredivise]] in his career at Utrecht.

===Swansea City===
On 10 August 2011, it was confirmed Vorm had joined [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] for a fee of around <U+00A3>1.5 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2011/aug/07/swansea-michel-vorm-utrecht|title=Swansea agree fee for Dutch international goalkeeper Michel Vorm|date=7 August 2011|work=Guardian|accessdate=23 August 2011|location=London}}</ref>
He took the number one role and made his debut for the club against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] on 15 August 2011 in a 4&ndash;0 defeat.<ref>http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=318034&cc=5901</ref> Although he conceded four goals, he also made eleven saves, more than any other Premier League goalkeeper, in a single game, in the whole of the 2010<U+2013>11 season. In his second match for Swansea against [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]], on 20 August, Vorm saved a 72nd minute penalty from Wigan's [[Ben Watson (footballer)|Ben Watson]], to give Swansea their first ever point in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/14514711.stm | work=BBC News | title=Swansea 0-0 Wigan | date=20 August 2011}}</ref> On 6 November 2011, Vorm arguably saved Swansea from defeat against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and earned them the draw at [[Anfield]] by pulling off two outstanding saves to earn the clean sheet. On 10 December, with Swansea 1<U+2013>0 up, he again saved a penalty in the 87th minute from Fulham's [[Clint Dempsey]] and finishing the game with another clean sheet.And to date (7.1.2012) he has kept nine clean sheets in the English premier league which is only second to Manchester United.

==International career==
In [[2006]] he was a member of the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] squad that won the [[UEFA U-21 Championship 2006]] in [[Portugal]].

As of 2008, Vorm is a member of the Dutch National Team. He made his debut in the starting lineup on September 5, 2009 in a friendly home match against [[Japan national football team|Japan]] (3<U+2013>0 win), followed up four days later by an impressive performance at [[Hampden Park]] during the [[FIFA World Cup qualification|World Cup qualifier]] [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] <U+2013> Netherlands, a match won by the Netherlands with 0<U+2013>1.<ref>[http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2009/sep/09/world-cup-scotland-holland] <U+2013> Holland end luckless Scotland's World Cup hopes <U+2013> September 9, 2009</ref><ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/internationals/8240464.stm] <U+2013> BBC Sports Scotland 0<U+2013>1 Netherlands  <U+2013> September 9, 2009</ref>
The match at Hampden Park was Vorm's first competitive game ever outside the Netherlands.<ref>[http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2009/sep/08/scotland-holland-maarten-stekelenburg-goalkeeper] <U+2013> Novice Dutch goalkeeper offers Scots glimmer of hope <U+2013> September 8, 2009</ref>

===2010 World Cup===
Vorm was included in the preliminary squad for the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]] in [[South Africa]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5iO9bETRJh0iovmmUN7ZeFDugTEIg |title=Van Marwijk trims Dutch squad to 27 | publisher=AFP|date=15 May 2010 |accessdate=18 May 2010 }}</ref> On 27 May 2010, Netherlands manager [[Bert van Marwijk]] announced that the player would be part of the final squad of 23 participating in the FIFA World Cup.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2010/may/27/holland-world-cup-23-man-squad |title=Holland coach Bert van Marwijk finalises World Cup squad |publisher=The Guardian |date=27 May 2010 |agency=Press Association |accessdate=27 May 2010 |location=London}}</ref> Before the start of the competition he was allowed to fly back to the Netherlands. During the World Cup, Vorm's girlfriend Daisy delivered a son, Jaivy Waylon. The Dutch goalkeeper returned home for two days following his son's birth.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/1049/Oranje/article/detail/490374/2010/06/14/Zoontje-voor-doelman-Vorm-Jaivy-Waylon.dhtml |title=Zoontje voor doelman Vorm: Jaivy Waylon |publisher=AD.nl|date=14 June 2010 |accessdate=7 July 2010| language =Dutch}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtl.nl/%28/actueel/rtlboulevard/nieuws/articleview/%29/components/actueel/rtlboulevard/2010/06_juni/entertainment/Op_babybezoek_bij_michel_vorm.xml |title=Op babybezoek bij Oranje-keeper Michel Vorm |publisher=RTL.nl| date=16 June 2010 |accessdate=7 July 2010| language=Dutch}}</ref>

